{
  "text": "As a subpart of the place branding, studies on city branding extend across academicians and practitioners in the last three decades [CITATION_1] , since cities all over the world engage in marketing and branding efforts in order to stay competitive and relevant on the global market [CITATION_2] . Such cities-also countries and regions-are no longer viewed just as touristic destinations. With the globalization and free and easy movement of capital, goods, and people, cities compete with each other to attract workforce, residents, and investors as well as tourists [CITATION_3] .",
